VIRTUAL INSTRUCTION INFORMATION:

Grades 6-12 will receive instruction through Edmentum Online Courseware.

Grades K-5 will receive instruction from a BES teacher in their grade level. Teachers will communicate to students via Google Classroom to share instruction that follows what is being taught in the classroom each day.

Students who choose the virtual option of instruction may participate in extracurricular activities and athletics as long as they meet the eligibility standards of the school and the IHSAA.

Please contact your student’s school for more detailed information.

post_text: Thank you for your patience and understanding as we have been developing a Reopening of School Plan that promotes our first priority of keeping our students and staff healthy and safe. A detailed plan will be shared on Wednesday, July 15th. The plan will detail items such as prevention, transportation, entering school buildings, cafeteria, hallway traffic, classroom teaching and learning, protecting vulnerable populations, and protocols outlining the steps to be followed if someone exhibits symptoms at school. A link will also be provided for those students who wish to participate in virtual instruction. We will have a Covid-19 link on our website that will have all pertinent documents and information specific to each school.

post_text:
REOPENING OF SCHOOLS UPDATE
We have been following the Indiana Department of Education, CDC, Indiana Department of Health, Governor’s Office, Jackson County Health Department, and our attorneys for guidance on the reopening of schools. Several meetings that will take place next week should put us well on our way to developing our reopening strategy. I will be meeting with all Jackson County Superintendents on Monday to discuss this topic. Other meetings include our Corporation Technology Team on Tuesday, Discussion Team on Wednesday, and a Reopening Team Meeting on Thursday. The Reopening Meeting will be attended by all administrators, directors, and representatives from the Teacher’s Association (BCCTA). We will share details of our reopening plan as they are developed. Thank you for you patience and support as we develop a safe and healthy plan for our students and staff.
text:
REOPENING OF SCHOOLS UPDATE
We have been following the Indiana Department of Education, CDC, Indiana Department of Health, Governor’s Office, Jackson County Health Department, and our attorneys for guidance on the reopening of schools. Several meetings that will take place next week should put us well on our way to developing our reopening strategy. I will be meeting with all Jackson County Superintendents on Monday to discuss this topic. Other meetings include our Corporation Technology Team on Tuesday, Discussion Team on Wednesday, and a Reopening Team Meeting on Thursday. The Reopening Meeting will be attended by all administrators, directors, and representatives from the Teacher’s Association (BCCTA). We will share details of our reopening plan as they are developed. Thank you for you patience and support as we develop a safe and healthy plan for our students and staff.

post_text: Brownstown Central Community Schools cares deeply for the well-being of our students, as is evident by the nearly 25,000 free meals that were delivered to our students’ doorsteps during the school closure due to Covid-19. Additionally, our community is served through the efforts of our Fellowship of Christian Athletes’ Shed for You. Please understand that recent meal price increases were mandated by the federal government in order for our school system to continue to receive funding of our student meal program.

May 8 at 11:32 AM ·

Aloha!

Brownstown Elementary School celebrated the end of the school year with a Hawaiian-themed parade Thursday evening, giving students a chance to see their teachers and other staff members for the final time of the school year. It was a unique end of the school year with students being instructed via eLearning due to the COVID-19 pandemic.

Look for the story in an upcoming issue of The Tribune and online at tribtown.com.

post_text:
TEACHER APPRECIATION WEEK

It’s only appropriate that on the last day of school, we look back to the first day of school on which every staff member received a Most Valuable Person award for the 2019-2020 school year. We knew without question that our staff would be deserving of these awards, but had no idea the conditions under which they would earn them. Thank you for proving not only to be the Most Valuable People, but also the Most Versatile People!

post_text:
This afternoon, Governor Holcomb closed Indiana schools through May 1st as a precautionary measure against the Covid-19 (Corona) virus. BCCSC will observe Spring Break next week (March 23-27). Our school buildings will also be under a mandatory shutdown that week.

From March 30-May 1 we will observe the following schedule:

Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday will be eLearning Days.

Monday and Friday will be Waiver Days (NO School)

A calendar will be shared at a later date.

Other items:

All Standardized State Testing is cancelled.

The IHSAA Boys’ Basketball Tournament has been cancelled.

The BCHS Prom has been rescheduled for Friday May 8th, if school is in session at that time.

The BCHS Class of 2020 Graduation remains scheduled for Saturday, May 23rd.

Please continue to follow all proper personal hygiene guidelines.

Thank you to our students, parents, teachers, counselors, administrators, and support staff for your flexibility, patience, and understanding. We intend to deliver the best learning opportunities possible to our students during these trying times.
text:

Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday will be eLearning Days.

Monday and Friday will be Waiver Days (NO School)

A calendar will be shared at a later date.

Other items:

All Standardized State Testing is cancelled.

The IHSAA Boys’ Basketball Tournament has been cancelled.

The BCHS Prom has been rescheduled for Friday May 8th, if school is in session at that time.

The BCHS Class of 2020 Graduation remains scheduled for Saturday, May 23rd.

Please continue to follow all proper personal hygiene guidelines.

Thank you to our students, parents, teachers, counselors, administrators, and support staff for your flexibility, patience, and understanding. We intend to deliver the best learning opportunities possible to our students during these trying times.

February 3-7 is National School Counseling Week. We would like to recognize Jill Miller, Alicia McCrary, Jami Stuckwisch, and Derrick Koch for their contributions to our schools and our students. Please seek these individuals out and share your appreciation for what they do.

A few synonyms for counselor include: advocate, instructor, mentor, teacher, counsel, and guide.

Thank you for filling these roles and many others for our students!

post_text: Congratulations, BCHS JAG!
shared_text:
Brownstown Central High School JAG
January 23 at 5:00 PM ·

🏆 BCHS JAG brought home some hardware 🏆

Students competed at our regional Career Development Conference today held at Hanover College.

Those pictured are:
Jada Terry- Creative Solutions
Sage Bennett-Critical Thinking
Emma Johnson- Writing Skills
Indiana’s First Lady- Janet Holcomb
Tiara Edwards- Employability Skills
Jennifer Catalan- Career Presentation
Sabra Bennett- Public Speaking
Rachel Hildebrand- Financial Literacy
Desiree Steinkamp- BCHS JAG Specialist

Everyone walked away with great learning experiences and had the chance to meet JAG students from all across Southeastern Indiana!

Tiara placed FIRST in Employability Skills and will represent BCHS and Region 9 at the State competition in March.

Rachel placed SECOND in Financial Literacy and Emma placed THIRD in Writing Skills.

We are so proud of everyone’s efforts and preparation for a successful event.
#JAGConnectsandEngages #BCHSJAG

Tiara Edwards- Employability Skills
Jennifer Catalan- Career Presentation
Sabra Bennett- Public Speaking
Rachel Hildebrand- Financial Literacy
Desiree Steinkamp- BCHS JAG Specialist

Everyone walked away with great learning experiences and had the chance to meet JAG students from all across Southeastern Indiana!

Tiara placed FIRST in Employability Skills and will represent BCHS and Region 9 at the State competition in March.

Rachel placed SECOND in Financial Literacy and Emma placed THIRD in Writing Skills.

We are so proud of everyone’s efforts and preparation for a successful event.

shared_text:
Brownstown Central High School
December 6, 2019 at 10:46 AM ·

post_text: Please send up some positive thoughts for BCHS staff member Kayia Davis.
shared_text:
Jodi Tiemeyer is with Kylene Barker Steward and 3 others.
November 30, 2019 at 11:20 AM ·

Update on Kayia Davis:
Kayia is in stable, but still critical condition in Indy hospital. She has a broken lower leg and heel that will require multiple surgeries, but her leg is stabilized for now. She also had some internal bleeding and had surgery to repair that in her abdomen. That is also stable, but will require some more surgery. She had some swelling of the brain, so they made a small opening for her brain to expand and put a drain tube in. That went well and she is recovering from that now. She is moving hands, legs, toes, etc when stimulated, which is good. They are managing her pain well and her vitals look good. Right now her body just needs time to heal and recover.
There is still a lot to get done, but Kayia is a fighter. Brent is with her and she has had family and friends up there as well. Please continue praying for healing.
